00:10:21,690 --> 00:10:22,510
The Last Supper.

279
00:10:22,509 --> 00:10:23,092
SPEAKER 1: OK.

280
00:10:23,092 --> 00:10:23,860
So not you.

281
00:10:23,860 --> 00:10:24,529
SPEAKER 2: Not me at all.

282
00:10:24,529 --> 00:10:25,740
SPEAKER 1: Someone
who can really draw.

283
00:10:25,740 --> 00:10:26,239
OK.

284
00:10:26,239 --> 00:10:28,194
So here is Leonardo's
Last Supper.

285
00:10:28,193 --> 00:10:29,610
Immediately, the
interesting thing

286
00:10:29,610 --> 00:10:32,810
is that after Brunelleschi
discovers linear perspective,

287
00:10:32,809 --> 00:10:34,729
artists like Masaccio
begin to use it.

288
00:10:34,730 --> 00:10:36,822
But they realize
that in addition

289
00:10:36,822 --> 00:10:38,279
to creating an
illusion of space it

290
00:10:38,279 --> 00:10:40,720
has a way of
bringing the viewer's

291
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:42,600
attention to the
vanishing point.

292
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:46,629
So artists begin to use it not
just to create that illusion,

293
00:10:46,629 --> 00:10:48,240
but they begin to
use it expressively.

294
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:50,320
And that's what we really
see here with Leonardo.

295
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:52,180
SPEAKER 2: So not only
is Leonardo creating

296
00:10:52,179 --> 00:10:54,289
this beautiful
perspectival space,

297
00:10:54,289 --> 00:10:56,360
but he's also
focusing our attention

298
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:59,822
on Jesus Christ at the center
who is the vanishing point.

299
00:10:59,822 --> 00:11:00,529
SPEAKER 1: Right.

300
00:11:00,529 --> 00:11:03,929
It brings our eye, our
attention to the divine.

301
00:11:03,929 --> 00:11:06,284
SPEAKER 2: So here we see
Leonardo's Last Supper,

302
00:11:06,284 --> 00:11:09,079
and we can certainly
just intuitively make out

303
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:11,370
the orthogonals and
the vanishing point.

304
00:11:11,370 --> 00:11:13,659
But let's go down and
really look at the diagram.

305
00:11:13,659 --> 00:11:14,242
SPEAKER 1: OK.

306
00:11:14,243 --> 00:11:15,169
Here we are.

307
00:11:15,168 --> 00:11:16,460
SPEAKER 2: So it's interesting.

308
00:11:16,460 --> 00:11:20,790
Their eye level all across is
basically at the horizon line.

309
00:11:20,789 --> 00:11:22,539
And of course, we see
the vanishing point,

310
00:11:22,539 --> 00:11:25,939
the point where all of
the orthogonals intersect,

311
00:11:25,940 --> 00:11:28,080
which is right here.

312
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:30,290
And so we have all
of these lines that

313
00:11:30,289 --> 00:11:34,279
are moving across the
surface of this wall,

314
00:11:34,279 --> 00:11:36,480
and they are all
bringing our eye right

315
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:38,529
to Jesus Christ in the center.

